<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="528" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="131.[1442,2649,724,1348]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1444,1801,1083,1112]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List. The Large-headed White-toothed Shrew is relatively uncommon, with the largest population in Tai National Park in Ivory Coast. It is threatened by habitat destruction and fragmentation, especially in Nigeria and Ghana.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
